@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "ColorBarr" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is a Workbench with at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  ColorBarr starts with the main menu, where you can choose the order in
which you want to play the game levels (either in the @{b}Normal@{ub} or
in a @{b}Random@{ub} order). When you are ready to play, just click the
@{b}Play!!@{ub} button.

  Playing with ColorBarr is very simple: just click on one of the arrows,
each of these arrows will move the tiles in that direction by one position.
If a tile is located on an edge of the board (either at left, right, up or
down) it will go on the opposite side. If a tile would move to an empty
space. it will jump over that space and go to the next tile position. Note
that if there is only one tile in a row (or column), there are no
corresponding arrows.

  The goal of the game is to recreate 8 rows of coloured tiles in such a way
that each row has tiles of the same colour. Try to complete each of the game
levels in the least amount of moves.

  Each game level has its own particularity. Some boards have a rectangular
shape, others have irregular shapes. Some rows may have a few tiles where
other rows have 15 tiles. Some game levels are arranged in such a way that
to get a tile at a certain position, you have to move that tile a couple of
rows higher, then move it some spaces horizontally and... you get the idea!

  Most of the time, you can place the coloured tiles where you want, the
only exception is that 2 different rows can have tiles of the same colour,
or that the number of tiles of a certain colour may only go to a particular
row because that row is the only one that has exactly the same number of
tiles. So you will have to decide where each type of tile will go on which
row.

  When you complete a level, the game displays how many moves you made and
goes to the next level. If you complete the 25 game levels, ColorBarr
displays the total amount of moves you made in the game and the average
number of moves in each level.

  You can always abort a game level by clicking on the closebutton, this
will return you to the main menu.

  Have fun!

@endnode

